3 Quaere, Whether Christ be not denyed in our estates, when his cause calls for something that we have, and we will part with nothing; the Lord hath need of our Ass, but we will not let him go, Mat. 21.3. When the cause of God stood in need, they parted with their gold and silver, pleasant things, and precious jewels, 1 Chron. 29.7, 8, 9. The question at Christs Tribunal will be too many men; didst not thou remember that such a year my cause lay at stake, and thou wouldst do nothing for me? It is all one with many, (as in the proverb) whether the Dog bite the Bear, or the Bear the Dog; whether the Churches stand or fall; 
                  Merosh was curst, because they came not to help the Lord against the mighty.
               Judges 5.23.
